Req. ID: 285465 
As a Supply Chain Planning Manager at Micron Technology, Inc., you will be responsible for managing supply in response to signals from Demand Management / Marketing / Sales supporting quarterly revenue plans. This manager will lead a team responsible for matching demand, capacity, and supply to meet customer requirements and cover business objectives. You are ultimately responsible for the success of your regional team and to ensure Business Unit and corporate objectives are met through global collaboration with partners internal and external to supply chain. This includes ensuring inventory targets, customer commitments, and overall production goals and objectives are met. You will work with Global Operations to enable efficient use of capacity and communicate with the Sales and Manufacturing teams to address areas where the supply may be adjusted to better satisfy demand. You will also work with Management on creation of metrics and continuously drive process improvement and accountability to these metrics throughout the supply chain. 
Role Responsibilities & Tasks Drive Strategy and Deliver Results 
Contribute as a member of the Supply Chain leadership team 
Develop strategic direction and provide guidance on key milestones, measurements, and objectives 
Track projects/progress and provide accountability 
Establish a strong network and relationships with partner organizations 
Establish goals and conduct performance appraisals â€“ focused on developing a world class planning team 
Manage employee performance and resolve conflicts 
Prioritize/assign work, remove barriers, and drive for accountability 
Develop strategy and action plans to ensure team activities are actively supporting and achieving strategic objectives 
Promote partnership across functional areas and customer groups 
Provide guidance to senior management on headcount and staffing requirements to enable a world class team supporting key business objectives 
Orchestrate multiple processes across cross functional teams 
Ensure alignment of overall supply capabilities are aligned with expectations and supporting business plans. 
Drive alignment in process and purpose across all Supply teams
 Ensure Communication and Knowledge Transfer with Manufacturing, Sales, and Marketing 
Provide input into the Quarterly Sales Plan, including available supply, recommended inventory levels, supply risk and opportunity, and manufacturing challenges to support revenue plans 
Act as key point of contact regarding supply questions from Sales/BU senior leadership 
Provide guidance to Manufacturing, including notification of Sales priorities, changes, and risks, Sales requirements that cannot be driven through systemic means, and cross-product family priorities 
Communicate with direct customers and external partners by providing input to Sales and Manufacturing 
Communicate with partners to ensure contract adherence and trade-offs 
Drive accountability for established R&Rs across partner organizations 
Coordinate establishment of business practices and processes with partners 
Education: 
Bachelor degree in Industrial Engineering, Supply Chain, or related field 
MS in Engineering or MBA preferred 
Experience:
 5+ years experience in Supply Chain desired
 Previous leadership experience a plus. 
Experience with JDA/Blue Yonder software desired 
